<task id="AUTHV2-064" project="Spaarke Auth v2 + Hardening">
  <metadata>
    <title>Refresh token rotation integration test</title>
    <phase>D — Reasonable security hardening</phase>
    <tags>security, library, tests, STANDARD</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>1 hour</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>Phase A</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>D-Parallel-1</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>MSAL handles RT rotation by default. Add an integration test that confirms it actually happens (catches regression if Microsoft changes defaults).</prompt>
  <role>Test engineer.</role>
  <goal>Test that triggers an MSAL silent refresh and verifies the new RT differs from the old RT.</goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.Auth/tests/ (test directory)</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Mock MSAL response to include refresh_token_1.</step>
    <step>Trigger acquireTokenSilent → expect MSAL to use RT1, get back AT2 + RT2.</step>
    <step>Assert RT2 !== RT1.</step>
    <step>Document the test purpose in a comment.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Test exists and passes.</criterion>
    <criterion>Test would fail if MSAL stops rotating RTs.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
